def: Relating to wheels or to rotary motion; rotary. [R.]

Having or covering an angle wider than the ordinary; -- appliedto certain lenses of relatively short focus. Lenses for ordinarypurposes have an angle of 50ยบ or less. Wide-angle lenses may cover asmuch as 100ยบ and are useful for photographing at short range, but thepictures appear distorted.
A great quantity or number. [Prov. Eng.]There was a mort of merrymaking. Dickens.

The portion of the upper crust of a loaf which has touchedanother loaf in baking. Lamb.A massy fragment from the rich kissingcrust that hangs like a frettedcornice from the upper half of the loaf. W. Howitt.
An optical instrument or toy for showing the presistence of animpression upon the eyes after the luminous object is withdrawn.
